      • fromFunction

        public static <T> java.util.function.Predicate<T> fromFunction(java.util.function.Function<T,java.lang.Boolean> function)
        Converts a function into a predicate. Functions return boxed booleans instead of primitives, and thus can return a null. The returned predicate returns true if the function returns true and false otherwise, so a null function result is considered false.
        Parameters:
        function - a function
        Returns:
        the specified function converted to a predicate
